    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/50182</id>
    <published>2011-11-15T00:00:00+00:00</published>
    <updated>2012-12-11T17:23:24+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/business-plan-2011-2015"/>
    <title>Business plan: 2011 to 2015</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>Business plan for the Ministry of Defence, 2011 to 2015.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;abbr title="Ministry of Defence"&gt;MOD&lt;/abbr&gt;’s 2012 to 2015 business plan sets out the programme of work we plan to carry out over the next 3 years to support the coalition government’s objectives. It also contains information on our structure and budget, and the way we measure our performance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Structural Reform Plan section can be viewed on &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.number10.gov.uk/transparency"&gt;Number 10 transparency&lt;/a&gt;, with information on the current status of each action, and explanations for any deadlines missed, updated monthly. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This year’s business plan is an update of the business plan published in May 2011. In addition, the annexes detail additional actions that support cross government priorities, and list completed actions from the 2011 business plan. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The changes from the 2011 business plan are highlighted in the 2011 business plan revisions document.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Monthly updates on the implementation of the structural reform plan element of the &lt;abbr title="Ministry of Defence"&gt;MOD&lt;/abbr&gt; business plan are also provided.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
